(2014) identified compound heterozygosity for the A100S mutation (616146.0001) and a c.700T-C transition, resulting in a tyr234-to-his (Y234H) substitution at a highly conserved residue within 1 of the TGDS loops. The Y234H mutation was not found in public variant databases. The unaffected parents were each heterozygous for 1 of the mutations. The N298D mutation was not found in public variant databases; the 2-bp deletion was present in heterozygous state in 2 of 2,132 individuals of African descent in the Exome Sequencing Project database and in 4 of 61,447 individuals in the Exome Aggregation Consortium database.
